### RDS Setup

```bash
# Create RDS instance
aws rds create-db-instance \
  --db-instance-identifier hospital-postgres \
  --engine postgres \
  --engine-version 15.3 \
  --db-instance-class db.t3.micro \
  --allocated-storage 100 \
  --master-username postgres \
  --master-user-password $DB_PASSWORD \
  --db-name hospital_gateway \
  --publicly-accessible false

# Get endpoint
aws rds describe-db-instances \
  --db-instance-identifier hospital-postgres \
  --query 'DBInstances[0].Endpoint.Address'
```

### ElastiCache Setup

```bash
# Create Redis cluster
aws elasticache create-cache-cluster \
  --cache-cluster-id hospital-redis \
  --engine redis \
  --engine-version 7.0 \
  --cache-node-type cache.t3.micro \
  --num-cache-nodes 1

# Get endpoint
aws elasticache describe-cache-clusters \
  --cache-cluster-id hospital-redis \
  --show-cache-node-info
```

## Health Checks & Monitoring

### Health Endpoints

```bash
# Liveness (is process running?)
GET /health/live

# Readiness (can accept requests?)
GET /health/ready

# Full health check
GET /health
```

### Prometheus Metrics

```typescript
// Future: Add metrics endpoint
GET /metrics
```

Output format:
```
# HELP hospital_gateway_requests_total Total requests
# TYPE hospital_gateway_requests_total counter
hospital_gateway_requests_total{method="POST",endpoint="/v1/chat"} 1234

# HELP hospital_gateway_escalations_total Total escalations
# TYPE hospital_gateway_escalations_total counter
hospital_gateway_escalations_total 56

# HELP hospital_gateway_quality_score Average quality score
# TYPE hospital_gateway_quality_score gauge
hospital_gateway_quality_score 0.87
```

### Logging

All requests logged with:
- Timestamp
- Correlation ID
- User ID
- Endpoint
- Method
- Status code
- Response time
- Errors (if any)

### Alerting

Suggested alerts:
- API response time > 5s
- Error rate > 5%
- Database connection failures
- Redis connection failures
- Escalation rate > 30%

## Zero-Downtime Deployment

### Rolling Update

```bash
# Update image
docker pull hospital-gateway:4.1.0

# Graceful shutdown (10s timeout)
docker stop -t 10 hospital-gateway

# Start new version
docker run -d hospital-gateway:4.1.0
```

### Blue-Green Deployment

```bash
# 1. Run new version (green)
docker run -d --name hospital-gateway-green hospital-gateway:4.1.0

# 2. Test green
curl http://localhost:3001/health

# 3. Switch traffic (update reverse proxy/load balancer)
# nginx: upstream_server = hospital-gateway-green:3000

# 4. Keep old version (blue) for rollback
docker rename hospital-gateway hospital-gateway-blue

# 5. Rename green to production
docker rename hospital-gateway-green hospital-gateway
```

## Backup & Recovery

### Database Backup

```bash
# Regular backup
0 2 * * * pg_dump hospital_gateway | gzip > /backups/hospital-$(date +%Y%m%d).sql.gz

# Point-in-time recovery
pg_basebackup -D /backup/base -Ft -z -P -U postgres

# Restore
gunzip < hospital-20240101.sql.gz | psql hospital_gateway
```

### Redis Backup

```bash
# Enable AOF (append-only file)
# redis.conf: appendonly yes

# Backup RDB
docker exec hospital-redis redis-cli BGSAVE
docker cp hospital-redis:/data/dump.rdb ./redis-backup.rdb

# Restore
docker cp redis-backup.rdb hospital-redis:/data/dump.rdb
docker restart hospital-redis
```

## Performance Tuning

### PostgreSQL

```sql
-- Increase connection pool
max_connections = 200

-- Buffer pool
shared_buffers = 256MB
effective_cache_size = 1GB

-- WAL settings
wal_buffers = 16MB
checkpoint_completion_target = 0.9
```

### Redis

```conf
# Eviction policy
maxmemory-policy allkeys-lru

# Persistence
appendonly yes
appendfsync everysec

# Client output buffer
client-output-buffer-limit normal 0 0 0
```

### Application

```typescript
// Increase pool sizes
const pgClient = new PgClient({
  max: 50,    // Was 10
  min: 10     // Was 2
})
```

## Troubleshooting

### Service Won't Start

```bash
# Check logs
docker logs hospital-gateway

# Check connectivity
docker exec hospital-gateway nc -zv postgres 5432
docker exec hospital-gateway nc -zv redis 6379

# Check env vars
docker exec hospital-gateway env | grep DATABASE
```

### High Latency

```bash
# Check database
psql -h db -U postgres -c "SELECT * FROM pg_stat_statements ORDER BY mean_exec_time DESC LIMIT 5;"

# Check Redis
redis-cli --latency
redis-cli --bigkeys

# Check network
docker exec hospital-gateway curl -w "@curl-format.txt" https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/models
```

### Memory Issues

```bash
# Monitor container memory
docker stats hospital-gateway

# Node heap snapshot
node --inspect dist/server.js
# Visit chrome://inspect

# Identify leaks
pnpm add -D clinic
clinic doctor -- pnpm start
```

